tennis. More than 65 colleges are being support</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ed by the Tennis Development Managers and we are seeing </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">an increase </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in the number of students picking up a racket.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="47" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Tennis Foundation is</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> working closely with the Association of Colleges and Sport England to ensure our offer meets the needs of the Furt</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">her Education sector. The Tennis Foundation and LTA are one of six NGBs supporting the Women’s Sport and Fitness Foundation (WSFF) with a specific project to ensure sport reaches, appeals to and retains female students in Further Education colleges.  We wi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ll be supporting this pilot during the autumn term 2013 involving research and intervention at three colleges, and will be encouraging College Sport Makers to introduce the adapted versions of Short Tennis and Cardio Tennis alongside flexible formats to he</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">lp more female students play tennis more often.  This pilot will support the Tennis Foundation and LTA’s Further Education Tennis Programme and our plans to increase female participation in tennis.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="48" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The support available through the University Tennis progr</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">amme, re-launched in September 2011, aims to grow the game, by creating more opportunities for students to play and compete. It also aims to provide students with the latest training packages, for those that have an ambition to become part of the future wo</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">rkforce for British tennis.  More than 44 universities are being supported through this programme.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="49" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">British tennis is</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> promoting Short Tennis and Cardio Tennis as suitable products to increase female participation in tennis, and the flexible options give co</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">lleges and universities opportunities to deliver activity on site and pathways to community sites be they clubs, local parks or community venues.  </span></li></ol><h4 style="font-weight:normal; line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt 0pt 4pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify